The `simp` tactic is powerful enough to handle these simplifications directly. The `<;> try { tauto }` and `<;> try { aesop }` are fallbacks to handle any simple logical implications that might arise from the simplification. The multiple `<;> try { native_decide }` are to handle any decidable propositions that might remain after simplification.

